The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during a speech in Michigan. He begins by thanking the hosts and expressing gratitude for the ministries represented in the room. He brings greetings from President Donald Trump and praises the President for keeping his promises. Pence discusses the accomplishments of the Trump administration, including the strong economy, increased military strength, and support for Israel. He emphasizes the administration's commitment to religious freedom and protecting the sanctity of life. Pence also criticizes the Democratic Party for its leftward turn and advocates for the re-election of President Trump. He encourages the audience to use their voices and pray for the nation.